  m_Name: ray
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::FishData
  <fishName>k__BackingField: Ray
  <fishFact>k__BackingField: "Rays are essentially flattened sharks that took up
    life on the seafloor. They glide through the water by rippling their wide, wing-like
    fins in a motion that looks almost like slow-motion flying. Most species are
    completely harmless, filter-feeding or hunting mollusks buried in sand, which
    they crush with flat, plate-like teeth. Some rays can also generate electricity
    \u2014 using it to sense their environment and stun prey. "
